    </num>
    <head>
      AVAILABILITY OF INFORMATION TO THE PUBLIC
    </head>
    <text>
      <AUTH>
        <HD SOURCE='HED'>
          Authority:
        </HD>
        <P>
          <aref type='USC'>
            <subref title='5' sect='301' note='' psec='' tq='N' target='http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/5/301.html'>
              5 U.S.C. 301
            </subref>
             and 
            <subref title='5' sect='552' psec='' tq='N' target='http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/5/552.html'>
              552
            </subref>
          </aref>
          ; 5 U.S.C. App.
        </P>
      </AUTH>
      <SOURCE>
        <HD SOURCE='HED'>
          Source:
        </HD>
        <P>
          <aref type='FREGIST'>
            60 FR 52842
          </aref>
          , Oct. 11, 1995, unless otherwise noted.
        </P>
      </SOURCE>
    </text>
    <section orderid='15908'>
      <extid>
        lii:cfr:2013:7:0:B:XXVI:-:2620:-:2620.1
      </extid>
      <num st='1'>
        2620.1
      </num>
      <head>
        General statement.
      </head>
      <citation />
      <contents>
        <SECTNO>
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='2620' sect='1' psec='' tq='N'>
              2620.1
            </subref>
          </aref>
        </SECTNO>
        <SUBJECT>
          General statement.
        </SUBJECT>
        <P>
          This part is issued in accordance with, and subject to, the
          regulations of the Secretary of Agriculture 
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='1' sect='1' psec='' tq='N'>
              1.1
            </subref>
          </aref>
           through 
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='1' sect='23' psec='' tq='N'>
              1.23
            </subref>
          </aref>
           (and appendix A of subpart A of 
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-PART'>
            part 
            <subref title='7' part='1' tq='N'>
              1
            </subref>
          </aref>
          ) of this title, implementing the Freedom of Information Act, 
          <aref type='USC'>
            <subref title='5' sect='552' note='' psec='' tq='N' target='http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/5/552.html'>
              5 U.S.C. 552
            </subref>
          </aref>
          , and governs the availability of records of the Office of Inspector
          General (OIG) to the public upon request.
        </P>
      </contents>
    </section>
    <section orderid='15909'>
      <extid>
        lii:cfr:2013:7:0:B:XXVI:-:2620:-:2620.2
      </extid>
      <num st='1'>
        2620.2
      </num>
      <head>
        Public inspection and copying.
      </head>
      <citation />
      <contents>
        <SECTNO>
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='2620' sect='2' psec='' tq='N'>
              2620.2
            </subref>
          </aref>
        </SECTNO>
        <SUBJECT>
          Public inspection and copying.
        </SUBJECT>
        <P>
          <aref type='USC'>
            <subref title='5' sect='522' note='' psec='#a_2' tq='N' target='http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/5/522.html#a_2'>
              5 U.S.C. 522(a)(2)
            </subref>
          </aref>
           requires that certain materials be made available for public
          inspection and copying, and that a current index of these materials be
          published quarterly or otherwise made available. OIG does not maintain
          any materials within the scope of these requirements.
        </P>
      </contents>
    </section>
    <section orderid='15910'>
      <extid>
        lii:cfr:2013:7:0:B:XXVI:-:2620:-:2620.3
      </extid>
      <num st='1'>
        2620.3
      </num>
      <head>
        Requests.
      </head>
      <citation />
      <contents>
        <SECTNO>
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='2620' sect='3' psec='' tq='N'>
              2620.3
            </subref>
          </aref>
        </SECTNO>
        <SUBJECT>
          Requests.
        </SUBJECT>
        <P>
          <npcatch lev='1' id='a'>
            <enum src='gpotxt' cln='1'>
              (a)
            </enum>
          </npcatch>
          <text>
             Requests for OIG records shall be in writing in accordance with 
            <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
              § 
              <subref title='7' part='1' sect='6' psec='#a' tq='N'>
                1.6(a)
              </subref>
               of this title
            </aref>
             and addressed to the Assistant Inspector General for Policy
            Development and Resources Management (AIG/PD&amp;RM), Office of
            Inspector General, U.S. Department of Agriculture, Ag Box 2310,
            Washington, DC 20250. The above official is hereby delegated
            authority to make determinations regarding such requests in
            accordance with 
            <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
              § 
              <subref title='7' part='1' sect='3' psec='#a_3' tq='N'>
                1.3(a)(3)
              </subref>
               of this title
            </aref>
            .
          </text>
        </P>
        <P>
          <npcatch lev='1' id='b'>
            <enum src='gpotxt' cln='1'>
              (b)
            </enum>
          </npcatch>
          <text>
             Requests should be reasonably specific in identifying the record
            requested and should include the name, address, and telephone number
            of the requester.
          </text>
        </P>
        <P>
          <npcatch lev='1' id='c'>
            <enum src='gpotxt' cln='1'>
              (c)
            </enum>
          </npcatch>
          <text>
             Available records may be inspected and copied in the office of the
            AIG/PD&amp;RM, from 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. local time on regular
            working days or may be obtained by mail. Copies will 
            <PRTPAGE P='85' />
            be provided upon payment of applicable fees, unless waived or
            reduced, in accordance with the Department&apos;s fee schedule as
            set forth in appendix A of subpart A of 
            <aref type='CFR-TIC-PART'>
              part 
              <subref title='7' part='1' tq='N'>
                1 of this title
              </subref>
            </aref>
            .
          </text>
        </P>
      </contents>
    </section>
    <section orderid='15911'>
      <extid>
        lii:cfr:2013:7:0:B:XXVI:-:2620:-:2620.4
      </extid>
      <num st='1'>
        2620.4
      </num>
      <head>
        Denials.
      </head>
      <citation />
      <contents>
        <SECTNO>
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='2620' sect='4' psec='' tq='N'>
              2620.4
            </subref>
          </aref>
        </SECTNO>
        <SUBJECT>
          Denials.
        </SUBJECT>
        <P>
          If the AIG/PD&amp;RM determines that a requested record is exempt from
          mandatory disclosure and that discretionary release would be improper,
          the AIG/PD&amp;RM shall give written notice of denial in accordance
          with 
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='1' sect='8' psec='#a' tq='N'>
              1.8(a)
            </subref>
             of this title
          </aref>
          .
        </P>
      </contents>
    </section>
    <section orderid='15912'>
      <extid>
        lii:cfr:2013:7:0:B:XXVI:-:2620:-:2620.5
      </extid>
      <num st='1'>
        2620.5
      </num>
      <head>
        Appeals.
      </head>
      <citation />
      <contents>
        <SECTNO>
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='2620' sect='5' psec='' tq='N'>
              2620.5
            </subref>
          </aref>
        </SECTNO>
        <SUBJECT>
          Appeals.
        </SUBJECT>
        <P>
          The denial of a requested record may be appealed in accordance with 
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='1' sect='6' psec='#e' tq='N'>
              1.6(e)
            </subref>
             of this title
          </aref>
          . Appeals shall be addressed to the Inspector General, U.S. Department
          of Agriculture, Ag Box 2301, Washington, DC 20250. The Inspector
          General will give prompt notice of the determination concerning an
          appeal in accordance with 
          <aref type='CFR-TIC-SECT'>
            § 
            <subref title='7' part='1' sect='8' psec='#d' tq='N'>
              1.8(d)
            </subref>
             of this title
          </aref>
          .
        </P>
      </contents>
    </section>
